  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This study is designed to answer a key question in the field of implementation science.
      Specifically, it seeks to determine if a proposed model for the implementation and scale-up
      of healthcare innovations (the AIDED model) is effective and useful. To fully evaluate the
      potential of this model, the investigators will conduct a multi-year study comprising 3
      phases. This proposal represents the first of these phases.
    </textblock>
